Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.50,0:00:14.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A man died while fighting the monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.79,0:00:18.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And just like in the game, \Nhe revived at the Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:20.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.32,0:00:22.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I came back to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.11,0:00:23.42,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.42,0:00:24.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.82,0:00:26.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.41,0:00:30.98,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The MMORPG {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.86,0:00:35.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Without warning, an estimated thirty \Nthousand Japanese alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.45,0:00:38.51,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and several hundred thousand worldwide,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:41.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,were trapped in a world just like the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.01,0:00:46.27,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And in this world, death is not the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.52,0:02:22.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Astral Bind!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:28.00,SignA,S,0000,0000,0000,,Slice
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.59,0:02:31.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.75,0:02:33.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it quits for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.43,0:02:35.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:41.55,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our bodies seem to know the \Nbasic combat movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.96,0:02:44.33,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we don't use commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.33,0:02:48.05,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as we intend to fight, \Nand can see the enemy in front of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.05,0:02:51.15,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,we can use skills and magic in a \Nmanner similar to voice input.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:57.24,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a difference between \N"using" and "mastering."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:00.47,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need some practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:07.11,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I don't know if practicing the way \Nmartial artists do in our world will be enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.61,0:03:09.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord Shiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.13,0:03:13.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, would you stop calling me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.28,0:03:14.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Just call me Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.53,0:03:17.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then I hope you'll treat me \Nwith the same familiarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.10,0:03:21.80,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You two sure are enjoying the height of youth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:23.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:29.68,Title1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1738,1)}The Battle of Loka
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.42,0:03:31.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.48,0:03:36.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ahead, to reconnoiter on our way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.29,0:03:37.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:38.86,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.47,0:03:42.04,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,One of the assassin's skills is Dark Vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.52,0:03:45.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And I also have Sneak and Silent Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:48.52,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This forest is the perfect place to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:50.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.55,0:03:53.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll meet by the south gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.64,0:03:56.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stay illuminated using Magic Light as we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:03:57.64,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You can use that to find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.99,0:03:58.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.47,0:04:03.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Then Akatsuki's subclass is tracker?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.64,0:04:06.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't even hear the leaves rustle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.09,0:04:07.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,She's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.98,0:04:09.14,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.57,0:04:12.75,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The skills Akatsuki mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:17.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Sneak and Silent Move, are tracker skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:20.90,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tracker is a subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:24.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Players in {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1} can select
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.10,0:04:27.11,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,from twelve main combat classes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:30.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and then choose among any number of subclasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.15,0:04:33.28,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,An assassin and a tracker, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.28,0:04:35.03,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder she calls herself a ninja.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:37.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,She's a hardcore role-player.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:40.92,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, how many \Ndays have we been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:45.80,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Security in town is getting really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:47.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:49.79,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The rush to buy guild halls has calmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.79,0:04:52.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,and I suppose the balance of power in the city
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.31,0:04:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has been more or less established.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:58.06,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers in the larger guilds \Nwield their influence freely,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.06,0:05:01.67,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,and somehow, the smaller guilds \Nhave become even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:06.57,Default,Beast,0000,0000,0000,,They act like anyone not in their \Nown guild is an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:09.44,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no fighting in towns, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.92,0:05:12.67,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting wasn't allowed in the majority of towns
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.67,0:05:14.83,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,when {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1} was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.38,0:05:17.58,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,So if you fight in town,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.88,0:05:21.51,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,powerful enforcers called the Royal Guard appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.52,0:05:23.61,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And just like in the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.61,0:05:26.19,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,if you resist, they'll kill you without mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.00,0:05:29.92,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told there's a lot of low-level \Nfighting and harassment
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.92,0:05:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that doesn't quite count as combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.56,0:05:34.89,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,In the past few days, PKs have rapidly increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:37.14,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,PKs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:38.82,Default,Blue,0000,0000,0000,,Player killings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:40.65,Default,Blue,0000,0000,0000,,Or player killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.93,0:05:46.24,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They attack players, rather than monsters, \Nand then steal items and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.24,0:05:47.78,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's the worst thing you could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.75,0:05:52.13,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Outside of town, you can't use your mini-map,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.13,0:05:54.16,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,and you can't contact the Game Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:56.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And surprise attacks are far more effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.77,0:05:58.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's much less risky now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:06:00.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The pros and cons have reversed positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.85,0:06:03.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That must be why it's more common now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.57,0:06:05.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,How cowardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.16,0:06:08.75,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,If Akihabara keeps getting worse...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:12.36,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:14.81,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.15,0:06:17.27,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:18.48,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Naotsugu?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:20.97,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.97,0:06:27.60,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I was just so taken by Akatsuki's \Ncuteness, I forgot to breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:30.07,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:33.21,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Shiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.21,0:06:34.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:40.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you need to feel \Nso bound by duty all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.73,0:06:43.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, there's no need to hold back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.99,0:06:46.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:47.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, shrimp!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:49.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me a shrimp!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,See any gobs?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:54.35,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I like the one with the skull on his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.61,0:06:56.15,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's weird and cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.15,0:06:57.32,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.16,0:07:02.59,HUD1,N,0000,0000,0000,,Loka Hospital\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NLeague of Freedom Cities, Eastal/ Center Area \NField/ Monsters Present \NEntry Restrictions/ None \NEvents/ None Currently
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.84,0:07:09.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I sense something...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:10.36,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is it human?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:12.01,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:18.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:20.89,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You're always so quick with support.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.89,0:07:23.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what do we do, Strategist?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:26.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu, straight line formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.78,0:07:28.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our enemies are PKs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.27,0:07:29.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I have visual contact on four.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:31.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll determine their location.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.53,0:07:33.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:35.05,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Mind Bolt!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.66,0:07:37.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:38.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy sighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.21,0:07:41.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They have guts, turning to PKing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:45.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They miss their mommies so much, \Nthey turned into animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.95,0:07:47.39,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,One dressed like a fighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.39,0:07:48.78,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,two as thieves,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.78,0:07:50.40,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,one like a healer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:52.68,Rikopin,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Rikopin / Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.76,Stroganopp,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Stroganopp / Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:54.82,HUD1,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Mode/ {\c&H6860CA&}Combat
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:54.82,Smash,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Smash / Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.75,0:07:53.06,Default,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Leave everything you're carrying,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:54.82,Katsuomaru,PK,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuomaru / Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:54.82,Default,PK,0000,0000,0000,,and we won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:58.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If they're talking like that, \Nthey've read too much manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.02,0:08:00.85,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, they're human.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.27,0:08:01.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:04.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Crush them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.02,0:08:06.88,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,These guys attack people for fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.23,0:08:12.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, if someone else kills \Nthem, they can't complain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.81,0:08:16.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm willing to give them the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That is, if they can beat us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.26,0:08:22.85,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well said, Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:26.59,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,First target, the one in front, on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:27.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Draw the others' attention, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.84,0:08:28.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.16,0:08:32.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the fighter to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:34.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You take the mage!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.57,0:08:35.41,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:38.33,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Astral Bind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:43.56,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Astral Bind is only a basic root spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.26,0:08:46.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It just keeps the target from \Ncovering long distances,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.18,0:08:47.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and it doesn't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.93,0:08:50.30,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take the mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:51.71,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You get the warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:53.29,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.83,0:08:54.86,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Good call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.43,0:08:56.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:59.60,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu is a guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.87,0:09:02.60,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Anchor Howl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:03.69,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.32,0:09:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.20,0:09:10.93,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A guardian belongs to a group called tanks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.73,0:09:15.04,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,whose role is to protect their \Nallies by intercepting attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.09,0:09:17.19,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anchor Howl...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:21.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone affected by this skill \Nbecomes unable to ignore the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.73,0:09:25.22,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The second they try, they're hit \Nwith a powerful counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:27.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.30,0:09:29.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take him first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:32.21,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You won't break through my armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.66,0:09:39.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But Naotsugu's HP won't last \Nanother thirty seconds...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:41.31,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Electrical Fuzz!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.60,0:09:46.74,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,He's an enchanter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.74,0:09:48.08,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's that spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.08,0:09:49.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't hurt at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.24,0:09:52.44,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The enchanter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:55.01,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A magical attack class type.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.01,0:09:56.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But its attack power is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.96,0:09:59.07,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you trying to \Naccomplish with that spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:07.21,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thorn Bind Hostage!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:11.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.28,0:10:19.13,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thorn Bind Hostage...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.74,0:10:22.85,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It wraps a caster's enemies in shining thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:25.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And for every hit an ally lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.88,0:10:28.85,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the thorns explode, dealing 1,000 damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.47,0:10:31.48,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Enchanters aren't offensively powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:34.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But they can weaken an enemy's attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.49,0:10:36.49,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,or strengthen their allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:41.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,When all five thorns explode, \Nyou'll lose half your HP.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.49,0:10:42.50,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.50,0:10:43.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We need to heal...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:44.41,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Healer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:46.44,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,On its own, the class is helpless,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.95,0:10:49.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and can't do much without a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.99,0:10:52.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.91,0:10:54.80,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Your back's totally exposed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:58.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll win because we have \Na healer and you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:02.09,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Have fun crying in the Cathedral—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.89,0:11:07.50,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, healer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:09.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.90,0:11:12.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've put your healer to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:16.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, they've been asleep the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.00,0:11:18.52,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Astral Hypnos...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.52,0:11:21.74,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,A spell that puts the target to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.74,0:11:23.23,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you out first, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:24.74,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.36,0:11:27.51,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Anchor Howl hasn't worn off yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.51,0:11:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cra—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.74,0:11:31.65,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:33.31,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorcerer! Summoner!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:34.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use everything we have!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.03,0:11:37.35,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Blast them to ash!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.96,0:11:44.14,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Assassin...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:48.93,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,This class specializes in quick \Nelimination of the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:53.56,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu was targeted by a bind-type \Nmovement-restriction spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:56.77,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't notice any mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:12:01.79,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,When I said I had visual contact on four,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:04.72,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki understood what I meant,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:08.43,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and acted quickly to remove the \Nambushers hiding in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.59,0:12:12.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Insulting my lord's magic isn't wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:16.71,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You laughed at those small electric bursts,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.71,0:12:21.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,but those bright lights kept you \Nfrom seeing in the dark forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:23.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You never realized your healer was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.98,0:12:27.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Your teamwork is full of openings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.78,0:12:31.58,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You were too focused on the battle \Nto even watch your own HP,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.58,0:12:34.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,or keep an eye on the rest of the party's status.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:36.74,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Taking out your ambushers was easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:39.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Defeating us won't do any good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.91,0:12:41.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just revive in the Cathedral...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.52,0:12:42.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Want to try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.81,0:12:46.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:48.62,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I won't do it again! Please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:50.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.31,0:12:54.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You actually thought I'd say that, you—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.33,0:13:12.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Security really is getting bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.65,0:13:15.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like PKing is good for much profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:18.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand people being freaked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.99,0:13:22.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But there are other things they \Ncould do with their time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:23.54,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.89,0:13:24.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Boobs—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:29.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, may I knee this pervert in the face?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:32.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Ask before you do it! And while you're \Nat it, let me finish my sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.47,0:13:34.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You were going to say something else perverted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:36.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I was, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.02,0:13:38.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Other things to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:40.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.31,0:13:42.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.33,0:13:45.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No goal to live for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.43,0:13:48.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Taste aside, we have food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:52.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,By defeating low-level monsters, \Nyou can make money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.78,0:13:54.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,With that money, you can stay at an inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:59.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting isn't allowed in towns, so you \Ndon't have to fear for your life there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.62,0:14:03.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And even if you do die, you'll come back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.77,0:14:08.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,So you can survive in this world \Nwithout doing anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.02,0:14:10.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But can you really call that living?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:12.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Or is just not being dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.50,0:14:17.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So they've resorted to PKing \Nbecause there's nothing else to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:21.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They need something beyond staying \Nalive to occupy their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.24,0:14:25.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And they're getting it by hurting others?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:26.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:29.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's pretty pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.03,0:14:30.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:34.01,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not doing anything, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.44,0:14:36.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:41.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I don't really think \Nthings are getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:43.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It just seems that way
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because everyone still thinks of this as \Nthe same {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0} world they knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:54.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If it isn't that world, then security \Nwas an illusion from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:57.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:00.22,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.41,0:15:05.12,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to Susukino?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:06.86,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,On the day of the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of our members was going to Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.79,0:15:12.09,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A girl called Serara...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:13.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.63,0:15:16.56,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The transport gates still aren't working, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.07,0:15:20.31,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Using fairy rings would be \Nthe only other way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:21.52,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:22.79,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we can't look up any online \Ntimetables in a walkthrough,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:29.61,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,using them is dangerous because we \Ncan't be sure where we'll end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.27,0:15:33.62,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the return spell, Call of Home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.97,0:15:37.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You can return to the last of the five \NGreat Cities you visited... Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:41.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The last one she visited was Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.25,0:15:42.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:45.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The only methods left are walking or by horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.58,0:15:50.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In the real world, there are 850 km \Nbetween Tokyo and Sapporo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.84,0:15:55.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0} world uses the Half Gaia Project,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.07,0:15:56.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,so it would be 425 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.70,0:16:01.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And during that time, you'd have \Nto fight monsters, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:04.93,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why send help now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.38,0:16:07.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.18,0:16:09.94,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,W-We've been planning to send \Na rescue team for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.31,0:16:11.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.21,0:16:14.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't look at me that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:16.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You look really mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:18.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, girls won't like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.04,0:16:27.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Things in Susukino are worse \Nthan they are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.60,0:16:28.42,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:33.20,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Some nasty players attacked Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:38.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She was lucky to be saved by a nice player.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:42.14,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Now they're protecting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.88,0:16:46.90,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And so, we were going to take our \Nhighest-level players to Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:52.53,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And I wanted to ask if you'd take care of \Nthe rest of the guild while we're away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:53.90,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.29,0:16:56.27,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Please... I beg you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.95,0:17:02.26,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty-one days is probably the fastest \Nyou can make it to Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:04.30,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Over a month, round trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.06,0:17:06.84,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance's \Nhighest-level members?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:10.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,In {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1}, the maximum party size is six.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.37,0:17:13.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If they had a good healer...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.09,0:17:18.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, their journey is going to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.16,0:17:21.19,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What's the best option, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:27.45,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,We... We should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.28,0:17:32.60,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I have no right to involve myself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.24,0:17:34.83,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,in someone else's guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.51,0:17:38.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And they wouldn't want that, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:42.87,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But... Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:45.79,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.90,0:17:50.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Say it, Shiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:52.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Your turn to speak, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:18:00.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:04.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The best option is for us to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:13.72,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ueno Thieves' Realm\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NLeague of Freedom Cities, Eastal/ Ueno \NField/ No Monsters\NDemihumans, Thieves Present \NEntry Restrictions/ None \NEvents/ None Currently
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.44,0:18:13.73,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, Naotsugu, Akatsuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.07,0:18:16.17,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Please save Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:18.74,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to us, and to my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:22.24,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A ninja does not know the word "failure."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:26.25,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Just like in the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:29.37,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,we were able to use items to summon horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.68,0:18:38.39,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you suppose these \Nhorses come from, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.39,0:18:43.14,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our bodies knew how to ride them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.29,0:18:49.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice that the movement is automatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.08,0:18:51.13,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,but it still hurts my butt...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:52.17,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.62,0:18:55.55,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's a really nice map.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:18:59.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,My subclass is scribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:02.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I made a copy of the maps at the archives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.30,0:19:04.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Nice job, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.47,0:19:06.41,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:07.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.86,0:19:10.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? I can't tell at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.42,0:19:13.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well... We'll make better \Ntime in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:14.52,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.54,0:19:20.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I just wish they could do \Nsomething about the food...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:23.30,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.57,0:19:27.55,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If someone you know is crying, you help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:29.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing unusual about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:30.82,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.82,0:19:32.61,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we have nothing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:35.15,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,that's no reason for us to be pathetic, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.64,0:19:36.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.62,0:19:41.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is my... It's our answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:43.16,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,What we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:45.90,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Or is that too cool for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:48.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:51.54,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's how cool it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.89,0:19:56.12,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our old place, the Debauchery Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.42,0:19:58.96,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.16,0:20:01.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.34,0:20:04.24,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What is that, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.83,0:20:22.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Those are griffons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:24.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:29.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't think we were going to \Nget to the far north on horses, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.06,0:20:34.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But these monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:34.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.37,0:20:37.82,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... W-We're riding them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.98,0:20:36.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:39.13,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We are, Miss Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:40.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.16,0:20:41.63,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:45.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A-Akatsuki... You'll ride behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.07,0:20:46.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.12,0:20:47.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.44,0:20:49.14,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:54.14,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard of summon flutes like those.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:57.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That they're only given to players
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.41,0:21:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who've won the Hades Breath \Nraid on the Fields of Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:03.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:06.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great trick to surprise people with!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:10.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Hop on, Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.21,0:21:27.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All set?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:29.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my lord, no problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:32.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, hang on tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:34.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, don't grab my stomach...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.60,0:21:35.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go first!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.67,0:21:43.26,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.84,0:21:44.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.18,0:21:46.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:48.20,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we'll get going, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.39,0:21:56.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great view.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.11,0:22:08.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.80,0:22:10.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.30,0:22:15.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord... This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.86,0:22:19.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we're floating in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.15,0:22:21.89,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this great?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.89,0:22:24.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing... This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.57,0:22:29.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The sky is so blue and clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.45,0:24:09.80,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe's party heads toward Susukino, \Nthrough the underground labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.80,0:24:12.61,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Awaiting them are phantoms of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.61,0:24:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a horde of rat-men.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.00,0:24:19.03,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,When Shiroe was a solo player, \Nhe once had friends he held very dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.03,0:24:22.94,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,They were called the Debauchery Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.27,0:24:30.99,Title1,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,The Depths of Palm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.59,0:24:25.82,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Depths of Palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.12,0:24:28.18,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,This is our reality.
